<CompareLayout
  title="kerfkit vs CutPlan (2026) — honest comparison"
  description="CutPlan is a solid web cut optimizer with 20+ languages and cloud sync. kerfkit is a native, fully offline app with an interactive Workshop Mode and a one-time price. Honest table inside.">

  <h1>kerfkit vs CutPlan</h1>
  <p>CutPlan is a capable web-based cut list optimizer with impressive language coverage and
  cloud-synced projects. kerfkit takes the opposite architectural bet: a native app that works
  entirely offline, with your data on your device and a one-time price. Which fits you depends
  on how — and where — you actually work.</p>

  <div class="tablo-sar">
  <table>
    <tr><th></th><th>kerfkit</th><th>CutPlan</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Platform</td><td class="iyi">Native iOS (Android on the way)</td><td class="notr">Web / PWA only — no native app, by their own account</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Works offline</td><td class="iyi">Fully — plan at the lumber yard, cut in a basement shop</td><td class="zayif">No — needs a connection</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Free tier</td><td class="iyi">Browser calculator: unlimited calculations, no signup</td><td class="notr">30 calculations per month</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Price</td><td class="iyi">One-time purchase. No subscription, ever</td><td class="zayif">$29/month, or $9 for a 2-day pass</td></tr>
    <tr><td>At-the-saw guidance</td><td class="iyi">Interactive Workshop Mode: glove-sized buttons, screen stays awake, tap-off each cut</td><td class="notr">Static step list (Pro)</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Grain, kerf, edge banding</td><td class="iyi">Yes — including banding meters</td><td class="iyi">Yes</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Fractional inches</td><td class="iyi">1/64″ fraction pad</td><td class="iyi">Yes</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Cloud sync</td><td class="zayif">Not in v1 — deliberate: your data never leaves the device</td><td class="iyi">Yes</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Offcut inventory</td><td class="zayif">Planned (v1.1)</td><td class="iyi">Yes</td></tr>
    <tr><td>DXF / CNC export</td><td class="zayif">Planned (v1.1)</td><td class="notr">Pro plan</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Languages</td><td class="notr">6 at launch, 20+ planned</td><td class="iyi">20+ today</td></tr>
  </table>
  </div>

  <div class="durust"><strong>Where CutPlan wins today:</strong> if you need cloud sync across
  many devices, offcut inventory right now, or a language we haven't shipped yet, CutPlan is
  the stronger pick — no spin. Our bet is that most woodworkers cut in places with sawdust and
  bad Wi-Fi, hate subscriptions, and want the phone at the saw — that's what kerfkit is built for.</div>
</CompareLayout>
